race.comment: SHE'S EXOTIC (4) won her fifth race from just eight starts when comfortably home in a similar event to this 15 days ago. Getting up in the weights but she had a fair bit in reserve last time so another win looks on the cards. MYSTERY LAD (1) shouldered 60.5kgs to victory two back over 1200m at Tamworth then disappointed in an open sprint at Coonamble last time. Nicely in after the claim so back in a Benchmark race he deserves another chance. LADY WARDELL (5) last appeared when third in a comparable race to this at Lismore eight weeks ago. Good fresh performer who rarely puts in a poor run. Must be considered. MY MUM'S TOYBOY (3) chased SHE'S EXOTIC home when resuming from a 191-day spell last start. Fitter and gets a weight swing so he can close the gap. SUPER IMPRESSIVE (8) has turned in a couple of real eye-catchers over five furlongs since returning from a spell. Will be hard to hold out over the extra 100m.
